{{infobox music festival | music_festival_name = K-Rock Dysfunctional Family Picnic | image = | caption = | location = [[New York City|New York, New York]] | years_active= 1997–2004, 2008 | founders=[[WNYL (FM)|K-Rock]] | dates = Summer | genre = [[Rock music|Rock]], [[Heavy metal music|Metal]], [[Punk music|Punk]], [[Hip hop music|Hip hop]], [[Post-hardcore]], [[Hip hop music|Rap]], [[Reggae]], [[Ska]] | website = [http://www.923krock.com 92.3 Krock] }} '''Dysfunctional Family Picnic''' was a multi-artist [[alternative rock]] concert, presented annually by the [[New York City|New York City, New York]], [[United States|USA]] radio station [[WNYL (FM)|K-Rock]], beginning in 1997. Its West Coast "sister" concert is the [[KROQ Weenie Roast]].
==History== There have been various venues that hosted the Dysfunctional Family Picnic including [[West Side Tennis Club|Forest Hills Tennis Stadium]] in [[Queens|Queens, New York]], [[PNC Bank Arts Center]] in [[Holmdel]], [[New Jersey]], [[Giants Stadium]], in [[East Rutherford]], [[New Jersey]] and [[Jones Beach Amphitheatre]] in [[Wantagh]], [[New York (state)|New York]].
In 2003, the Dysfunctional Family Pinic was called "DFP 7-Tarium". Instead of booking an original show, it was just another stop on [[Metallica]]'s [[Summer Sanitarium]] tour.
After K-Rock returned to the air in 2007, "Return of Rock" was their first concert.
