{{Refimprove|date=September 2018}} '''Indonesia Fair''' ({{lang-id|'''Pekan Raya Indonesia''' or '''PRI'''}}) is a [[fair]] held annually. The goal of the fair is to promote the growth of the economy of [[Indonesia]] through the [[Meetings, incentives, conferencing, exhibitions|MICE]] industry (meeting, incentive, convention, and exhibition ). The fair features exhibitions, trade promotions, shopping, music performances, various shows, [[amusement ride]]s and a food festival<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.thejakartapost.com/life/2018/09/02/pekan-raya-indonesia-returns-with-80-local-brands.html|title=Pekan Raya Indonesia returns with 80 local brands|newspaper=The Jakarta Post|accessdate=24 September 2018}}</ref>. Pekan Raya Indonesia (old spelling Pekan Raja Indonesia), or Indonesia Fair,{{sfn|Merrillees|2015|p=90}} was held for three consecutive years between 1953 and 1955. Then after a long gap it is being held every year at [[Indonesia Convention Exhibition|ICE]] at [[BSD City]], in [[Jabodetabek|Greater Jakarta]], [[Indonesia]] since 2016. The fair is usually held in the month of September and October.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://travel.kompas.com/read/2016/11/02/081500127/bedanya.pekan.raya.indonesia.dengan.pekan.raya.lainnya|title=Bedanya Pekan Raya Indonesia dengan Pekan Raya Lainnya|newspaper=Kompas|accessdate=24 September 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://properti.kompas.com/read/2018/02/21/090000721/pekan-raya-indonesia-kembali-digelar-tiketnya-rp-35.000|title=Pekan Raya Indonesia Kembali Digelar, Tiketnya Rp 35.000|newspaper=Kompas|accessdate=24 September 2018}}</ref> ==History== The first Pekan Raya Indonesia was held between 29 August to 4 October 1953, officially known as "The First Indonesian International Trade & Industrial Fair". China was the main international exhibitor. It was held on the site where [[Atma Jaya Catholic University of Indonesia|Atma Jaya University]] now stands, on what is then called Kebayoran Road (now [[Sudirman Road|Jalan Jendral Sudirman]]).{{sfn|Merrillees|2015|p=90}}
The second Pekan Raya Indonesia in 1954. The main international exhibitor was [[Soviet Union]].{{sfn|Merrillees|2015|p=91}}
The third Pekan Raya Indonesia was held in 1955 and the [[United States]] was the main international exhibitor. Leading US companies such as Ford, General Motors, Caterpillar, Goodyear, RCA and Pan Am took part in the fair. [[Holiday on Ice]] was first introduced to Indonesia through the Pekan Raya Indonesia 1955, whose performance in Jakarta was attended by then [[First Lady]] of USA, [[Eleanor Roosevelt]].{{sfn|Merrillees|2015|p=91}} Among other notable features of the fair was the ''Stand Televisi'' ("television stand"), among the first introduction of a true color television to Indonesia.
In 2016, PRI was held with the concept of 1,000 bands, 1,000 culinary tastes of the archipelago heritage, and a variety of family games that last from October 20 to November 6 2016<ref>{{cite news|url=https://properti.kompas.com/read/2016/10/20/190859321/pekan.raya.indonesia.2016.resmi.digelar|title=Pekan Raya Indonesia 2016 Resmi Digelar|newspaper=Kompas|accessdate=24 September 2018}}</ref>.
The 2017 Indonesian Fair (PRI) was held from October 21 to November 5, 2017, with a concept of richer Indonesian culture, starting from musical concert, culture, culinary, shopping, to multi-scale exhibitions<ref>{{cite news|url=https://metro.tempo.co/read/851655/pekan-raya-indonesia-2017-berlangsung-selama-16-hari|title=Pekan Raya Indonesia 2017 Berlangsung Selama 16 Hari|newspaper=Tempo|accessdate=24 September 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.liputan6.com/lifestyle/read/2873274/pekan-raya-indonesia-2017-manjakan-pecinta-belanja|title=Pekan Raya Indonesia 2017 Manjakan Pecinta Belanja|newspaper=Liputan 6|accessdate=24 September 2018}}</ref>.
2018 Indonesia Fair was held from September 27 to October 7, participated by 600 tenants with more than 2,000 trademarks. Participants ranges from property, automotive, fashion, food and beverage, and electronics sectors as well as creative businesses and small and medium enterprises. International Indie Music Festival (IIMF) was arranged as part of the festival.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.thejakartapost.com/news/2018/09/28/pekan-raya-indonesia-targets-1-million-visitors.html|title=Pekan Raya Indonesia targets 1 million visitors|newspaper=The Jakarta Post|accessdate=27 October 2018}}</ref>
