{{Orphan|date=November 2015}}

'''''Orlov let''''' ("Eagle's Flight") was the name of an anti-terrorist operation conducted by the Montenegrin police to arrest a group of [[Albanians]] who planned terrorist attacks and an armed conflict in Albanian-inhabited parts of [[Montenegro]]. The group of 17 people planned operations from 2004 to their arrest on the night of 10/11 September 2006. Weapons and explosive material were found in police raids. The group's main operative was the destroying of cultural and religious buildings (Orthodox) in Albanian-inhabited territory. The group was organised by an Albanian association based in [[Detroit]], and members of the [[Kosovo Liberation Army]], from which they received financial aid and [[smuggled arms]] into Montenegro. The group was given a total sentence of 51 years of prison. Relations between the state and the Albanian minority strained after the event.{{sfn|Morrison|2008|p=224}}

