{{italic title}} {{Use mdy dates|date=October 2011}} '''''Twain and Shaw Do Lunch''''', formerly known as '''''Shaw and Twain Do Lunch''''', was written by [[Chambers Stevens]]<ref>http://www.chambersstevens.com</ref> and made its world premiere at Miami's New Theatre in December 2011.<ref>[http://miamiherald.typepad.com/drama_queen/2011/05/new-theatre-picks-a-new-season.html New Theatre picks a new season | Drama Queen]. Miamiherald.typepad.com (May 18, 2011). Retrieved on October 20, 2011.</ref><ref>[http://florida.broadwayworld.com/article/NEW-THEATRE-Announces-Its-26th-Anniversary-Season-20110519 NEW THEATRE Announces Its 26th Anniversary Season]. Florida.broadwayworld.com. Retrieved on October 20, 2011.</ref> It is based on a real meeting between [[Mark Twain]] and [[George Bernard Shaw]].<ref>[http://www.twainquotes.com/19070630b.html Twain and British interviewers]. Twainquotes.com (June 30, 1907). Retrieved on October 20, 2011.</ref><ref>[http://www.fullbooks.com/Mark-Twain-A-Biography-1907-19101.html Mark Twain, A Biography, 1907–1910 by Albert Bigelow Paine – Full Text Free Book (Part 1/6)]. Fullbooks.com. Retrieved on October 20, 2011.</ref><ref>''Mr. Clemens and Mark Twain'' by Justin Kaplan. A Touchstone book. Page 382 paperback</ref> The full-length comedic play has won the Fourteenth Annual Long Beach Playhouse New Works Festival in Long Beach, CA,<ref>''The Desert Post Weekly'', "And the prize goes to..." by Marc Thompson on Thursday April 14, 2005</ref><ref>''The Desert Sun'', "Festival reveals 'the process' by Bruce Fessier, Saturday, April 16, 2005</ref><ref>http://www.lbph.com/NewWorks/ShawTwain.pdf</ref><ref>[http://search.barnesandnoble.com/Magnificent-Monologues-for-Teens/Chambers-Stevens/e/9781883995119 BARNES & NOBLE | Magnificent Monologues for Teens (Hollywood 101 Series): The Teens' Monologue Source for Every Occasion! by Chambers Stevens | NOOK Book (eBook), Paperback]. Search.barnesandnoble.com. Retrieved on October 20, 2011.</ref><ref>[http://www.broadwaytovegas.com/March14,2004.html Broadway To Vegas March 14, 2004]. Broadwaytovegas.com. Retrieved on October 20, 2011.</ref> the 2005 Palm Springs International Playwriting Festival for Best Comedy, and has also appeared in the Futurefest at the Dayton Playhouse.<ref>[http://www.browncreative.com/Godspell_mention_year_in_theater.htm Cover]. Browncreative.com. Retrieved on October 20, 2011.</ref>
